<title>FRANCE: France to tighten taxes on life assurance - paper.</title>
<headline>France to tighten taxes on life assurance - paper.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>France's conservative government is planning to tighten the tax treatment of life assurance policies next year, financial daily Les Echos reported on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The government is probably going to increase tax contributions to end early withdrawals from the policies, the paper said.</p>
<p>But the paper said the government has decided to leave in place the exemption on inherited proceeds from life assurance policies.</p>
<p>Government officials declined all comment on the newspaper report.</p>
